UML:TaggedValue.value: This package contains framework packages for information modelling. These include: - elements of the ISO 19100 series of standards relating to Geographic Information. Of particular interest are: - the General Feature Model (ISO 19109), an upper-level model or meta-model for information types, to be used as the basis for domain models presenting an object-centric view of spatial information - the Coverage model (ISO 19123) which provides an alternative property-centric view of spatial information - cross-domain utility classes, including basic types (ISO 19103), spatial schema (ISO 19107), temporal schema (ISO 19108), coordinate reference systems (ISO 19111) - elements required for registration and governance (ISO 19110, ISO 19135) - service descriptions and profiles (ISO 19119, ISO 19128, ISO 19132) - models associated with the OGC Sensor Web Enablement initiative - additional packages of cross-domain interest, which have not yet been formally adopted by a recognised governance authority, including - components from GML that do not correspond with ISO elements - extensions and specializations to ISO 19123 Coverage model - extensions to ISO 19107 spatial schema covering convex polyhedra, surfaces, curves

Collection of utilities that have not attained formal governance status, though in some cases they are on a standardization track. These are recommended best practice within the HollowWorld modelling framework.

This package to contain explanation of the nature of the HollowWorld modelling template. Currently incomplete and not properly synced. Also see https://www.seegrid.csiro.au/twiki/bin/view/AppSchemas/HollowWorld
